        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 3 at 10:58PM PDT by NWS Phoenix AZ</headline>
        <description>At 1057 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northwest of Midland, or 34 miles southwest of Highway 95 At
Mile Marker 29, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of Riverside County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Persons in campgrounds should consider seeking sturdy shelter until
this storm passes.</instruction>
